listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Cognizer</fen> is the one that makes a <fen>Judgment</fen>. This role is typically expressed as the External Argument (or in a <ment>by</ment>-PP in passives).
<fen>Evaluee</fen> is the person or thing that a judgment is made with respect to. With verbs this role is typically expressed as Object:
A description (from the point of view of the <fen>Cognizer</fen>) of the position of the <fen>Evaluee</fen> on a scale of approval.
The <fen>Offense</fen> is the action, crime, or event which is described in terms of what legal or punishing action can be taken against the offender.
This is the person whose <fen>Misdeed</fen> is being judged with respect to its morality.
The assessment of the <fen>Wrongdoer</fen> is based on his or her <fen>Misdeed</fen>.
The time at which a <fen>Misdeed</fen> is performed.
This is the person whose <fen>Behavior</fen> is being judged with respect to its morality.
The assessment of the <fen>Evaluee</fen> is based on his or her <fen>Behavior</fen>.
The <fen>Expressor</fen> is the body part or action by a body part which is the basis of the evaluation of morality.
The part of the <fen>Whole</fen> that is conceived as being broken or taken off from the remaining part of the whole.
The piece that is presented in a less prominent position, and which is the landmark or remaining whole from which <fen>Sub_part</fen> breaks off.
The time at which the breaking off of the <fen>Sub_part</fen> happens.
The location at which the breaking off occurs.
This is the person who is accused of a  <fen>Misdeed</fen>.
The wrongful act which  the <fen>Accused</fen> was purportedly involved in.
